1
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:17,400
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,680
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,160 --> 00:00:40,080
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,520
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 15]

23
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,290
Mr. Zheng, you wanted to see me?

24
00:01:53,790 --> 00:01:54,410
Right now,

25
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:55,820
drop the lawsuit against Guo Cong

26
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,050
and draft an apology letter to Customs.

27
00:01:58,760 --> 00:01:59,660
What's going on?

28
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,850
He's already been suspended.

29
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,820
This is our chance

30
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,540
to press our advantage.

31
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,690
What advantage?

32
00:02:05,710 --> 00:02:07,410
I'm about to lose everything here.

33
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:09,540
Just relax.

34
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:11,170
Tell me what's going on.

35
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:13,100
When you came to me for cooperation,

36
00:02:13,190 --> 00:02:13,850
my intention

37
00:02:13,870 --> 00:02:15,410
was to mess with Guo Cong and Customs.

38
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:16,380
But now, this whole thing

39
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,570
is hurting my interests.

40
00:02:18,150 --> 00:02:19,500
You guys have really screwed me over.

41
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,060
No way.

42
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,890
Public opinion is still on our side.

43
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:23,100
Those online trolls?

44
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,340
All they do is type some words

45
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,410
and vent for fun.

46
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:26,850
You think they spend a single cent?

47
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:29,260
But that warehouse video you released

48
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:30,890
has made my buyers think

49
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:32,380
the watch was actually tampered with.

50
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,820
The watch is in your possession.

51
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,100
Just explain it clearly to them.

52
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,100
Easy for you to say.

53
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,060
If they believed me,

54
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,410
I wouldn't be this stressed.

55
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:42,010
The problem is, they only trust Customs.

56
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:43,890
They're asking Customs to issue proof

57
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:45,450
that the watch was strictly secured

58
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,850
while under Customs custody.

59
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,060
So tell me,

60
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,690
how am I supposed to win this case now?

61
00:02:50,150 --> 00:02:51,570
Alright… I'll figure it out.

62
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:53,610
My dear lawyer,

63
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:54,540
I'm begging you.

64
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,610
Just drop it.

65
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,780
Because of this whole mess,

66
00:02:56,910 --> 00:02:58,290
not only did my previous buyer bail,

67
00:02:58,430 --> 00:03:00,060
but now people are piling on.

68
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,690
Some are saying
the watch has a shady origin,

69
00:03:01,710 --> 00:03:02,940
and the highest offer now
is only five million yuan.

70
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:05,130
I'm about to lose ten million here.

71
00:03:06,030 --> 00:03:07,100
The lawsuit must be withdrawn today.

72
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:09,260
You got your laptop with you?

73
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:09,980
No? Use mine.

74
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,940
Let me talk to my client first…

75
00:03:12,030 --> 00:03:13,730
Talk about what?

76
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,660
Withdraw it today.

77
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,260
I don't care what issues

78
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,570
your client and Customs have.

79
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:19,820
I'm not getting dragged

80
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,130
into this mess anymore.

81
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:28,820
Zheng Ting doesn't want to play anymore.

82
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,260
He pulled back the lawyer's letter.

83
00:03:31,470 --> 00:03:33,850
What the hell were you guys doing?

84
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:34,940
Bro…

85
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,660
I'm not your bro, okay?

86
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:38,690
What do you mean, he just pulled out?

87
00:03:38,870 --> 00:03:40,500
That lawyer is freaking useless.

88
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:44,170
Zheng Ting got scared that the watch
would be stuck in his hands.

89
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:45,380
So…

90
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:46,980
So what?

91
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,610
You guys just panic

92
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:50,100
the moment something happens.

93
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:50,890
Listen.

94
00:03:50,910 --> 00:03:52,410
Don't tell Li about this.

95
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,890
She just started feeling relieved.

96
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,340
And one more thing,

97
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:58,410
clean up your own mess.

98
00:04:12,030 --> 00:04:12,610
He did it!

99
00:04:12,630 --> 00:04:13,500
He made a post!

100
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:14,410
What post?

101
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,660
Bonus announcement?

102
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:16,730
No.

103
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,810
Zheng Ting.

104
00:04:17,830 --> 00:04:19,170
The buyer of that fancy watch.

105
00:04:19,190 --> 00:04:20,220
He put out a statement

106
00:04:20,270 --> 00:04:21,700
and reposted

107
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:23,250
the Customs clarification.

108
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,020
Look, here.

109
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:28,490
"I, Zheng Ting, hereby declare

110
00:04:28,830 --> 00:04:30,900
that there was absolutely no misconduct

111
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:33,460
or unauthorized handling of the watch.

112
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:34,930
Such false claims

113
00:04:34,950 --> 00:04:37,290
have not only damaged the reputation

114
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:39,700
of Binhai Huayan Airport Customs
and the staff

115
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:42,050
but have also infringed
upon my legal rights.

116
00:04:42,070 --> 00:04:42,610
In this regard,

117
00:04:42,630 --> 00:04:43,540
I reserve the right

118
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,780
to pursue further legal action.

119
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:48,540
At the same time,

120
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,220
I would like to sincerely apologize

121
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,980
to Binhai Huayan Airport Customs

122
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,490
and the staff members involved,

123
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:54,930
who were dragged into this matter

124
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:56,220
due to my lack of vigilance.

125
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:59,610
I will also visit Customs
to offer my apology in person."

126
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:02,170
That shady trader

127
00:05:02,190 --> 00:05:03,730
suddenly found his conscience?

128
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:04,780
Pretty good with words, though.

129
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:07,490
This post from Zheng Ting

130
00:05:07,510 --> 00:05:09,290
is still trying to twist the narrative,

131
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:10,780
putting serious pressure

132
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,140
on our customs officers.

133
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:14,170
Didn't he mention the lawyer's letter?

134
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:14,980
He did.

135
00:05:15,510 --> 00:05:16,930
This one's for Customs.

136
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:17,780
The next post says

137
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:19,290
he has withdrawn the lawyer's letter

138
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:21,460
and apologizes specially to Mr. Guo.

139
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:23,370
So that means…

140
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,900
Mr. Guo can come back?

141
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:27,220
Logically, yes.

142
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,460
It's my phone!

143
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:32,980
Oh, my…

144
00:05:35,630 --> 00:05:37,610
We'll see what Customs says.

145
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,220
Anyway, good news. End of day.

146
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:43,930
Good news!

147
00:05:44,190 --> 00:05:45,050
Let's go.

148
00:05:45,070 --> 00:05:46,250
Clock out.

149
00:05:56,870 --> 00:05:57,810
Mr. Shen.

150
00:05:58,750 --> 00:05:59,810
What are you doing?

151
00:05:59,870 --> 00:06:00,460
Sir…

152
00:06:03,510 --> 00:06:04,610
I'm here…

153
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:06,250
For your mentor?

154
00:06:06,310 --> 00:06:07,050
Yes.

155
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,490
I actually came to ask

156
00:06:09,830 --> 00:06:11,610
if Mr. Guo can come back now.

157
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:12,780
But I feel like

158
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:14,100
he's not ready yet.

159
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,410
What do you mean?

160
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:17,410
He's a veteran customs officer.

161
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,490
Of course he knows

162
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:20,100
Zheng Ting can't win

163
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,410
a baseless lawsuit like this.

164
00:06:21,430 --> 00:06:23,220
The truth would come out eventually.

165
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,220
Then why did he…

166
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,980
Did you really study psychology?

167
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:28,580
Sit.

168
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,370
Sit down.

169
00:06:39,270 --> 00:06:40,140
Think about it.

170
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,540
We asked him to take leave.

171
00:06:49,430 --> 00:06:50,660
The lawyer's letter…

172
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:52,610
That was…

173
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:53,780
just an excuse?

174
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:55,730
Exactly.

175
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,220
Ever since Chen's passing,

176
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,490
Guo Cong's been wound tight
like a spring.

177
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:03,540
Day and night, he stayed
in the Passenger Inspection Hall.

178
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,540
You've seen it, right?

179
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:06,900
So I think

180
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:09,220
he's pushing himself this hard

181
00:07:09,310 --> 00:07:10,020
because

182
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,610
he can't let it go.

183
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:15,100
Guo Cong is a qualified
passenger inspection officer.

184
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,410
Dedicated, responsible.

185
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,980
Now that he's run into trouble,

186
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:18,850
we won't

187
00:07:18,950 --> 00:07:20,140
just sit back and do nothing.

188
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,370
You guys

189
00:07:21,630 --> 00:07:23,700
deal with huge crowds every day.

190
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,610
When something happens,

191
00:07:24,630 --> 00:07:25,810
it's hard to find an outlet.

192
00:07:26,310 --> 00:07:28,170
So we need to give him

193
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,460
some time alone.

194
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,050
I believe

195
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,810
he'll sort things out.

196
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:48,340
Xiang,

197
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:50,580
if you need anything, just tell me.

198
00:07:50,830 --> 00:07:51,780
I'm good. Don't let me keep you.

199
00:07:55,630 --> 00:07:56,730
Alright, Cong.

200
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:57,730
Stop scrubbing.

201
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:58,930
You're gonna

202
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:00,700
scrub a hole right through my pot.

203
00:08:00,870 --> 00:08:03,340
Go talk with Uncle Xiang for a bit.

204
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:04,610
Just go.

205
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,540
Cong,

206
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,610
you've been busy since I got here.

207
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,780
Tao came all this way to see you,

208
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,170
and you're not even talking with us.

209
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:20,340
Thanks.

210
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:26,730
Let me have a word with him.

211
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,300
So…

212
00:08:33,630 --> 00:08:35,010
those Customs approval procedures,

213
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:36,060
when will they come through?

214
00:08:36,790 --> 00:08:38,460
I've never handled this before.

215
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,940
Not sure how long it'll take.

216
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,180
It needs to be fast.

217
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,770
It's student vacation season.

218
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:45,060
We gotta book flights and hotels.

219
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,340
Mr. Xiang,

220
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,130
are you heading abroad?

221
00:08:49,910 --> 00:08:51,940
I want Cong to come with me
to clear his head a bit.

222
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:53,700
Got any destination?

223
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:55,770
Australia.

224
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,730
At first, I was thinking of Sydney.

225
00:08:58,270 --> 00:08:59,420
Convenient.

226
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:00,340
But then

227
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,250
he said he'd had enough of the sea.

228
00:09:02,550 --> 00:09:04,580
So I figured, let's go a bit farther.

229
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:08,060
We'll drive to Uluru National Park.

230
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,060
See that…

231
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:11,100
that big red rock—Ayers Rock.

232
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,010
I fly there all the time.

233
00:09:13,030 --> 00:09:13,850
- Know it inside out. - Hey.

234
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:16,730
My food's here.

235
00:09:16,790 --> 00:09:17,700
Gotta take care of that.

236
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:18,370
You guys carry on.

237
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:21,650
Over there.

238
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:22,530
Okay.

239
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,300
Tao,

240
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,490
Cong's mentor

241
00:09:49,510 --> 00:09:50,490
just passed away.

242
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:52,580
So the way he is…

243
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,580
Don't take it personally.

244
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:54,820
It's okay.

245
00:09:55,910 --> 00:09:57,580
I know things are tough for him.

246
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:58,980
So

247
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:01,250
I want to do my part, too.

248
00:10:04,790 --> 00:10:06,490
How about this, Mr. Xiang?

249
00:10:06,910 --> 00:10:08,730
If you don't mind,

250
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:10,580
could I join you on the Australia trip?

251
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:12,420
I know that place really well.

252
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,580
And I've got many friends there.

253
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:16,100
I might even be able to be your guide.

254
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,220
Sure.

255
00:10:18,510 --> 00:10:19,850
If your schedule works out,

256
00:10:19,870 --> 00:10:20,940
we can go together.

257
00:10:22,030 --> 00:10:22,820
Look at him.

258
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:24,700
He's completely shut off right now.

259
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:26,730
I don't want to disturb him either.

260
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,300
If you

261
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,100
come with us,

262
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:30,820
at least I'll have someone to talk to.

263
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,370
That'd be nice.

264
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,060
It's my pleasure.

265
00:10:33,270 --> 00:10:34,770
My schedule's no problem.

266
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:35,730
I've got annual leave.

267
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:37,850
I can swap shifts if needed.

268
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:39,850
But this

269
00:10:39,870 --> 00:10:41,300
stays between us.

270
00:10:41,550 --> 00:10:42,770
Otherwise, I can't help you.

271
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,420
We'll figure out the rest
once we get to Australia.

272
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,220
Okay.

273
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:01,460
Cong,

274
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:03,530
not into that girl?

275
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,530
Right now?

276
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:12,250
Not the time. Not in the mood.

277
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,010
Try to open up a bit.

278
00:11:15,270 --> 00:11:17,770
Don't just focus
on what's right in front of you.

279
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:22,890
Lift your head and look around.

280
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:24,220
There's a whole wide world out there.

281
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,490
The meaning of life

282
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:30,340
isn't just about work.

283
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,940
I don't want Chen's regrets

284
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:33,610
to become

285
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:35,460
yours one day.

286
00:11:38,550 --> 00:11:40,060
My mentor's regrets…

287
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:42,130
were caused by me.

288
00:11:44,670 --> 00:11:46,890
You're giving yourself too much credit.

289
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:49,060
His regrets

290
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:50,770
were his own choice.

291
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:52,220
No one else to blame.

292
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:53,700
Same with me.

293
00:11:54,030 --> 00:11:55,730
I followed him from the plateau

294
00:11:55,910 --> 00:11:57,580
all the way to the coast.

295
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,250
No regrets.

296
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:09,100
Hello, Mr. Xiang.

297
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,100
Hi, Zhang.

298
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:12,420
Hi.

299
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,250
Looking for your mentor?

300
00:12:13,270 --> 00:12:14,580
Yeah, something came up at Customs.

301
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,770
I'll go talk to him.

302
00:12:15,910 --> 00:12:17,180
Isn't he on leave?

303
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,890
It won't take long.

304
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,340
I'll head over then.

305
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:21,940
I'll leave you to it.

306
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:22,700
Alright.

307
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:28,340
Fei.

308
00:12:28,550 --> 00:12:29,490
Hi, Zhang.

309
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,370
What are you doing here?

310
00:12:33,030 --> 00:12:33,980
Something happened at Customs?

311
00:12:34,150 --> 00:12:34,940
Nothing.

312
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:38,300
Can't I just come visit Fei?

313
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,980
Only you're allowed to come here?

314
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:44,250
I love it when Zhang comes here.

315
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:45,770
Whenever you show up,

316
00:12:45,790 --> 00:12:46,820
it makes my day.

317
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:47,820
Of course.

318
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:48,420
Look,

319
00:12:48,510 --> 00:12:50,650
you run a seafood place,

320
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:51,530
and me?

321
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,300
I'm your lucky catch from the sea.
[*'Zhang Yu' sounds like 'octopus'.]

322
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:55,130
I'm here to bring you some business.

323
00:13:00,630 --> 00:13:01,370
Mr. Xiang,

324
00:13:01,910 --> 00:13:02,940
I've got something to do.

325
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:03,890
I'm gonna head out.

326
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:05,940
I've got something, too.

327
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:06,730
Let's go say goodbye to her.

328
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:07,530
Then we'll go.

329
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,180
Can you?

330
00:13:12,910 --> 00:13:13,820
Of course.

331
00:13:15,510 --> 00:13:16,250
Fei,

332
00:13:16,670 --> 00:13:17,650
we've got something to do.

333
00:13:17,670 --> 00:13:18,940
We're heading out.

334
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:19,580
Okay.

335
00:13:20,390 --> 00:13:21,340
Cong's staying with you.

336
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:22,610
Keep an eye on him.

337
00:13:24,790 --> 00:13:25,890
He's an adult.

338
00:13:25,910 --> 00:13:27,180
He won't need me to.

339
00:13:28,030 --> 00:13:28,850
In a few days,

340
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,940
I've got a fishing boat coming in.

341
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,460
When there's fresh fish and shrimp,

342
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:33,420
I'll give you a call.

343
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:33,850
Sounds good.

344
00:13:33,910 --> 00:13:34,890
I'm in for a treat then.

345
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,220
Alright, we're heading out.

346
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,130
Mr. Xiang,

347
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,700
Australia's got tons of seafood, too.

348
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:42,610
When we get there,

349
00:13:42,630 --> 00:13:43,610
I'll take you to try some.

350
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,010
Zhang Yu is Cong's trainee.

351
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:49,490
Keep calm.

352
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,580
Got it, Mr. Xiang.

353
00:13:58,630 --> 00:13:59,420
Zhang,

354
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:01,420
since you're here,

355
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,420
spend some time with your mentor.

356
00:14:03,910 --> 00:14:04,820
Stay for dinner

357
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:06,060
with us tonight.

358
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,730
Sounds great. I won't say no.

359
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:08,220
Thanks.

360
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:08,890
Alright.

361
00:14:14,630 --> 00:14:15,650
Go on, what is it?

362
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:21,060
Zheng Ting dropped the lawsuit.

363
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:24,890
He also apologized online
to Customs and to you.

364
00:14:26,390 --> 00:14:27,130
That's good.

365
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:29,650
You and Xiaoyan can get out of this now.

366
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:31,300
We're fine.

367
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:34,250
I came this time mainly to ask you

368
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:35,610
when you're coming back.

369
00:14:41,790 --> 00:14:42,650
What's wrong?

370
00:14:44,390 --> 00:14:46,530
The accusation has been withdrawn.

371
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:50,980
We miss you.

372
00:14:52,910 --> 00:14:54,850
Maybe you can come back soon.

373
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,010
I'm thinking…

374
00:15:00,150 --> 00:15:01,300
of going to Australia.

375
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:06,370
Where? Australia?

376
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,180
Wait, what?

377
00:15:08,270 --> 00:15:08,730
What…

378
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:09,770
Why?

379
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:11,250
Australia?

380
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:12,610
Don't get worked up.

381
00:15:13,510 --> 00:15:14,650
I'm not worked up.

382
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:15,980
We've been running around
handling everything,

383
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,650
and suddenly you're saying
you're going to Australia?

384
00:15:17,670 --> 00:15:19,250
What's that supposed to mean, Mentor?

385
00:15:19,270 --> 00:15:20,490
Let me finish, okay?

386
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,580
Before my mentor passed,

387
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,250
I didn't fulfill

388
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,770
his only wish.

389
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,180
Looking back now,

390
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:33,940
I really was too impatient.

391
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:35,460
Customs asked me to take leave

392
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:37,300
so I could get myself back on track.

393
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,300
So…

394
00:15:38,870 --> 00:15:40,130
I still need some time

395
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:42,130
to figure out what to do next.

396
00:15:55,910 --> 00:15:57,300
No way, Mentor.

397
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:58,650
No way.

398
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:00,300
How could Mr. Chen

399
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:02,420
blame you over the Group E case?

400
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:05,010
You were his best apprentice.

401
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:06,180
Besides,

402
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:07,180
he was

403
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:08,610
seriously ill.

404
00:16:08,670 --> 00:16:11,060
We can't take everything
he said literally.

405
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:13,060
When we visited him last time,

406
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,490
he kept mistaking me for Fei,

407
00:16:14,510 --> 00:16:15,610
then for…

408
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:17,700
Deng.

409
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:18,530
You couldn't

410
00:16:18,550 --> 00:16:21,580
even tell who he was talking to.

411
00:16:22,790 --> 00:16:23,730
And you heard this

412
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:25,010
from Mr. Xiang, right?

413
00:16:25,030 --> 00:16:26,610
Mr. Xiang told you.

414
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:28,770
You weren't even there.

415
00:16:28,790 --> 00:16:30,610
How can you be so sure?

416
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:39,340
Let me show you something.

417
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:50,890
Before my mentor passed,

418
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:54,250
there was a brief moment

419
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:55,610
of terminal lucidity.

420
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:57,940
Director Huang said

421
00:16:58,390 --> 00:16:59,700
it's a final flash of clarity.

422
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:04,050
He said a lot to Uncle Xiang,

423
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:05,860
and he left me two words:

424
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,420
Let go.

425
00:17:08,790 --> 00:17:10,010
He didn't finish writing it,

426
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:11,980
but I can understand it.

427
00:17:13,750 --> 00:17:15,530
My mentor left this world

428
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:16,530
feeling powerless

429
00:17:17,030 --> 00:17:18,050
and full of regret.

430
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,010
Wait.

431
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:20,420
He didn't even finish writing it.

432
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:22,380
How can you be so sure
it means 'let go'?

433
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,620
How do you know?

434
00:17:24,110 --> 00:17:25,090
Even if it is 'let go',

435
00:17:25,110 --> 00:17:26,290
it could mean

436
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:28,090
'let go and fight',

437
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:28,730
or

438
00:17:29,310 --> 00:17:30,290
'let things take their course'.

439
00:17:30,310 --> 00:17:31,700
It could mean anything.

440
00:17:32,790 --> 00:17:34,420
Mentor, I think

441
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:36,570
the more regrets Mr. Chen had,

442
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,810
the more you should return to Customs.

443
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:39,900
You should go after the people

444
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:41,050
behind those dolls.

445
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:42,570
Make up for what he couldn't finish.

446
00:17:42,590 --> 00:17:43,980
He's gone!

447
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:45,810
It's too late!

448
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,530
Even if I make up for it,

449
00:17:47,550 --> 00:17:48,940
he won't see it anymore.

450
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,380
So you're chasing criminals,

451
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,570
cracking down on smuggling,
just for Mr. Chen?

452
00:17:57,590 --> 00:17:59,490
What about protecting the border?

453
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:01,980
Serving the people?

454
00:18:02,590 --> 00:18:03,420
Zhang Yu,

455
00:18:03,590 --> 00:18:04,940
don't get so worked up!

456
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:10,420
Words said in anger

457
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:11,490
won't help!

458
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:17,860
Zhang Yu,

459
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,330
you're better than me.

460
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:22,010
You've got more drive.

461
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,420
I hope you live without regrets.

462
00:18:33,750 --> 00:18:34,530
Childish.

463
00:18:35,350 --> 00:18:36,570
Your mentor just passed,

464
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:39,140
and you two are already fighting?

465
00:18:39,350 --> 00:18:40,220
Ridiculous!

466
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:41,090
Come with me.

467
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:46,290
Sit down.

468
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:47,140
Sit.

469
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:53,620
Zhang, why did you come today?

470
00:18:54,030 --> 00:18:56,810
To stab your mentor in the heart?

471
00:18:57,350 --> 00:18:58,140
Fei,

472
00:18:59,110 --> 00:19:01,330
I came to bring him good news,

473
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,810
and he threw cold water all over it.

474
00:19:03,830 --> 00:19:04,490
I didn't…

475
00:19:06,510 --> 00:19:07,290
Zhang…

476
00:19:08,110 --> 00:19:09,090
on this,

477
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:11,090
I still trust Cong.

478
00:19:12,030 --> 00:19:13,220
Calm down.

479
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:15,380
Don't blow up so easily.

480
00:19:16,590 --> 00:19:17,660
Now tell me,

481
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,530
what were you fighting about?

482
00:19:22,310 --> 00:19:25,010
He said Chen blamed him
for not completing the mission.

483
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:26,420
And he died with regrets.

484
00:19:26,830 --> 00:19:27,700
What?

485
00:19:31,110 --> 00:19:31,700
Let…

486
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:32,570
No,

487
00:19:32,750 --> 00:19:34,090
he didn't even finish writing it.

488
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:43,220
Cong,

489
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:45,420
look,

490
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:49,330
even if your mentor wrote this,

491
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:52,010
it might not have been meant for you.

492
00:19:52,790 --> 00:19:53,770
Don't just claim it.

493
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,220
And you, Zhang Yu.

494
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:01,420
It looks like you learned nothing

495
00:20:02,030 --> 00:20:03,730
but his fiery temper.

496
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:09,250
Zhang,

497
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,290
what Cong needs now is your support.

498
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:13,530
You understand?

499
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:15,220
Go home.

500
00:20:15,790 --> 00:20:16,620
I'll talk

501
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:17,730
to him later.

502
00:20:18,270 --> 00:20:18,980
Don't worry.

503
00:20:29,310 --> 00:20:29,900
Go.

504
00:20:34,550 --> 00:20:36,140
The moment I said it,

505
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:37,620
I regretted it.

506
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:39,660
I knew I'd gone too far.

507
00:20:40,550 --> 00:20:42,660
When I saw Zheng Ting's post,

508
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:45,980
I thought it was settled, overjoyed.

509
00:20:46,590 --> 00:20:49,140
But then, I rushed over here,

510
00:20:49,350 --> 00:20:51,220
only to have him dampen my spirits.

511
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:54,050
So I lost control of my temper.

512
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:57,330
Fei's right.

513
00:20:57,510 --> 00:20:59,380
I need to work on that.

514
00:20:59,880 --> 00:21:02,180
He needs my help right now.

515
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:09,200
[Safe and Sound]

516
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:28,050
Trash.

517
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:42,770
Okay, pick that up.

518
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:47,660
Give it to me.

519
00:21:50,550 --> 00:21:51,530
This one, too?

520
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:57,220
It's dirty.

521
00:21:57,830 --> 00:21:58,460
It's…

522
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:01,330
Give it to me. We don't need it.

523
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:04,620
Picking up trash. Fish need it.

524
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:09,330
Fish need it.

525
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:11,660
Yu needs it?
[*'Yu' sounds like 'fish' in Chinese.]

526
00:22:13,750 --> 00:22:15,460
Yu doesn't need it.

527
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:17,330
Zhang Yu doesn't need it.

528
00:22:20,270 --> 00:22:20,900
Fish.

529
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:23,420
Fish.

530
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:26,140
Fish in the water.

531
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:26,810
Yes.

532
00:22:27,790 --> 00:22:29,050
Picking up trash…

533
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:31,420
Fish need it.

534
00:23:05,510 --> 00:23:06,250
Trash…

535
00:23:07,350 --> 00:23:07,860
Fish…

536
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:28,940
Fei.

537
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:31,050
Coming.

538
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:33,330
You've been busy all day.

539
00:23:33,350 --> 00:23:34,860
Let's have a drink tonight.

540
00:23:35,070 --> 00:23:35,490
No.

541
00:23:57,590 --> 00:23:58,900
We have rules.

542
00:23:59,310 --> 00:24:00,140
No drinking.

543
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:02,290
Aren't you on leave?

544
00:24:02,750 --> 00:24:03,570
Besides,

545
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:06,330
first, we're not colleagues,

546
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:09,010
and second, we don't have
any financial connections.

547
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:10,010
It's fine.

548
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:15,980
Come on.

549
00:24:17,830 --> 00:24:18,660
This

550
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:21,460
is the first time the three of us
have had a drink together.

551
00:24:22,070 --> 00:24:22,700
Cheers.

552
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:37,140
Thanks.

553
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:41,980
Try this.

554
00:24:46,590 --> 00:24:47,290
Cong.

555
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:53,290
Do you know how many years

556
00:24:53,510 --> 00:24:54,770
this place has been open?

557
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,330
Do you know

558
00:24:57,350 --> 00:24:59,050
why it's called 'Fools' Dock'?

559
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:03,250
This restaurant

560
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:06,490
was opened the year
Chen came back to Binhai.

561
00:25:09,110 --> 00:25:10,860
The 'fool', actually, is me.

562
00:25:12,030 --> 00:25:13,290
Twenty-four years ago,

563
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:16,380
I followed him all the way to Guangdong.

564
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:17,660
And well,

565
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:20,140
that's how this place came to be.

566
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:25,490
But he worked at Customs.

567
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:27,490
That didn't stop you two

568
00:25:27,510 --> 00:25:29,090
from being together, right?

569
00:25:29,110 --> 00:25:30,220
No, it didn't.

570
00:25:31,270 --> 00:25:32,770
But your mentor

571
00:25:33,070 --> 00:25:35,140
had his own kind of twisted logic.

572
00:25:35,590 --> 00:25:36,380
He thought

573
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:37,460
that since he was someone

574
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:39,770
who took his job extremely seriously,

575
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:41,090
he couldn't give me

576
00:25:41,350 --> 00:25:44,460
the steady companionship I deserved.

577
00:25:44,790 --> 00:25:46,220
And his workaholic lifestyle

578
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:47,770
would bring me risk.

579
00:25:49,510 --> 00:25:50,620
Or maybe…

580
00:25:51,680 --> 00:25:53,050
someone like me

581
00:25:53,550 --> 00:25:56,380
just wasn't what he pictured

582
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:58,090
as the perfect wife.

583
00:25:58,440 --> 00:25:59,330
Honestly, Fei,

584
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,420
in my heart,

585
00:26:01,750 --> 00:26:02,810
you're a strong woman.

586
00:26:03,310 --> 00:26:04,490
You can take things on

587
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:06,010
and let things go.

588
00:26:06,310 --> 00:26:07,380
You live with dignity.

589
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:12,250
I'm someone who makes my own decisions.

590
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:15,770
Your mentor was afraid
he couldn't handle me.

591
00:26:18,310 --> 00:26:20,090
But true love

592
00:26:20,110 --> 00:26:20,860
isn't about

593
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:22,140
who controls whom,

594
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:24,180
or who gives in to whom.

595
00:26:24,550 --> 00:26:26,460
It's about walking hand in hand

596
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:28,570
through everything,
all the way to the end.

597
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:30,940
But by the time he figured that out,

598
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:34,010
we were already this age.

599
00:26:34,590 --> 00:26:36,730
Life just carried on.

600
00:26:37,480 --> 00:26:37,940
Drink.

601
00:26:44,550 --> 00:26:45,290
No wonder

602
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:48,090
he always

603
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:49,010
told me,

604
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,770
when he retired,

605
00:26:51,030 --> 00:26:52,330
he'd come work here for you.

606
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:55,140
Fei,

607
00:26:56,830 --> 00:26:57,860
you've really

608
00:26:58,510 --> 00:26:59,460
been through a lot.

609
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,290
Actually,

610
00:27:01,310 --> 00:27:02,220
this was our way

611
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:04,810
of being together.

612
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:06,770
As long as Chen got off work

613
00:27:06,790 --> 00:27:07,730
and didn't have anything else,

614
00:27:07,750 --> 00:27:09,460
he'd come here for a bowl of noodles.

615
00:27:10,070 --> 00:27:12,140
The two of us would sit

616
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:13,220
and chat for a bit.

617
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:14,980
When we were in a good mood,

618
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:16,530
we'd have a couple of drinks.

619
00:27:17,750 --> 00:27:18,860
Just the two of us.

620
00:27:20,310 --> 00:27:21,420
Thinking about it,

621
00:27:22,310 --> 00:27:23,770
it was actually beautiful.

622
00:27:25,750 --> 00:27:26,660
Come on, drink.

623
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:35,490
Oh, right.

624
00:27:35,920 --> 00:27:37,180
Let me show you something.

625
00:27:56,350 --> 00:27:57,180
Look.

626
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:00,490
These guys

627
00:28:00,920 --> 00:28:02,380
are your mentor's fellows.

628
00:28:02,550 --> 00:28:03,570
And this is my brother.

629
00:28:05,510 --> 00:28:07,090
I didn't know
about this connection of yours.

630
00:28:08,590 --> 00:28:10,860
Chen and my brother
were in the same unit.

631
00:28:11,030 --> 00:28:12,330
They stood guard together.

632
00:28:14,030 --> 00:28:14,620
See this?

633
00:28:15,350 --> 00:28:17,050
This was their squad leader.

634
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:18,460
He's from Shaanxi.

635
00:28:18,830 --> 00:28:20,010
And this is the guy

636
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:22,010
who taught me how to make noodles.

637
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:27,620
You were all young,

638
00:28:27,750 --> 00:28:28,770
and you were so pretty.

639
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,010
I… I didn't mean it like that…

640
00:28:32,030 --> 00:28:32,570
I mean…

641
00:28:32,590 --> 00:28:34,090
You're still pretty now.

642
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:37,420
Alright. I don't care at this age.

643
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:39,860
Fei…

644
00:28:40,350 --> 00:28:41,660
Don't you have any photos

645
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:43,140
of just you and my mentor?

646
00:28:43,270 --> 00:28:44,090
Yeah.

647
00:28:48,830 --> 00:28:49,620
Look.

648
00:28:54,790 --> 00:28:55,700
Actually,

649
00:28:56,510 --> 00:28:58,090
this one's my favorite.

650
00:28:58,790 --> 00:28:59,730
Because…

651
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:02,380
this is how we started.

652
00:29:03,110 --> 00:29:04,730
It was taken in Kamba.

653
00:29:17,590 --> 00:29:18,700
Later,

654
00:29:19,030 --> 00:29:20,250
your mentor

655
00:29:20,350 --> 00:29:21,620
brought Xiang over,

656
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:23,220
and then you.

657
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:26,050
He didn't have many friends.

658
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:28,420
Anyone he brought here

659
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:29,770
was family.

660
00:29:35,510 --> 00:29:36,290
Cong,

661
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:38,770
I've said all this today.

662
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:40,770
What

663
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:42,530
I want to say

664
00:29:43,070 --> 00:29:45,140
is that I'm the one
who understood Chen the best.

665
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:48,980
As long as he protected the border,
he had no regrets.

666
00:29:52,110 --> 00:29:53,730
But Uncle Xiang told me

667
00:29:54,270 --> 00:29:56,420
my mentor said it himself.

668
00:29:57,110 --> 00:29:58,090
He was ill.

669
00:29:58,110 --> 00:29:59,770
He couldn't even recognize me.

670
00:30:00,310 --> 00:30:02,380
Even if it was a moment of clarity,

671
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:04,380
he'd been confused for three years.

672
00:30:05,590 --> 00:30:06,900
In those three years,

673
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:08,860
no one knew what he was thinking, right?

674
00:30:10,920 --> 00:30:11,730
But…

675
00:30:12,550 --> 00:30:14,250
when he first entered the nursing home,

676
00:30:14,640 --> 00:30:15,900
I went to see him.

677
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:17,660
I told him

678
00:30:19,070 --> 00:30:20,490
I'd close this restaurant,

679
00:30:20,510 --> 00:30:21,860
and we'd buy a camper

680
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:24,220
and go on a road trip.

681
00:30:24,440 --> 00:30:25,620
Just the two of us.

682
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:28,420
We'd go as far as we could,

683
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:29,900
and I'd stay with him till the very end.

684
00:30:30,350 --> 00:30:31,570
Guess what he said?

685
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:35,700
He said

686
00:30:36,030 --> 00:30:37,330
he wanted to stay here

687
00:30:38,030 --> 00:30:40,140
so he could be your anchor.

688
00:30:40,750 --> 00:30:42,530
He felt that as long
as he was in Binhai,

689
00:30:42,550 --> 00:30:44,420
he could be your backbone.

690
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:46,220
See?

691
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:47,940
To him, what mattered more

692
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:49,250
was the process.

693
00:30:49,270 --> 00:30:50,730
It was about holding the line.

694
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:53,180
How could he possibly
tell you to let go?

695
00:30:55,750 --> 00:30:57,050
Maybe he…

696
00:30:58,310 --> 00:30:59,250
Cong.

697
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:02,380
I'm not in a position
to ask anything of you.

698
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:06,290
Stay the night if you have to.

699
00:31:06,790 --> 00:31:08,180
But don't come back tomorrow.

700
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,490
Fei, I just

701
00:31:12,750 --> 00:31:13,570
don't want to go home right now.

702
00:31:13,590 --> 00:31:15,290
That has nothing to do with me.

703
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:17,730
But you're not staying here.

704
00:31:18,030 --> 00:31:18,900
Why?

705
00:31:23,240 --> 00:31:24,490
At first, I thought

706
00:31:24,510 --> 00:31:26,250
you came here to heal.

707
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:27,810
But

708
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:29,940
you were just hiding,

709
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:32,140
avoiding this regret.

710
00:31:33,070 --> 00:31:34,290
If that's the case,

711
00:31:34,310 --> 00:31:35,620
I can't keep you here.

712
00:31:35,790 --> 00:31:38,380
Go do what you need to do.
Don't overthink it.

713
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:40,620
And one more thing.

714
00:31:41,070 --> 00:31:42,380
Chen is gone.

715
00:31:42,750 --> 00:31:43,770
I'm leaving, too.

716
00:31:44,550 --> 00:31:46,140
Same plan as before.

717
00:31:46,790 --> 00:31:48,050
I'll buy a camper

718
00:31:49,070 --> 00:31:51,380
and drive back to Kamba,
the place closest to the sky.

719
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:52,570
You're leaving?

720
00:31:58,750 --> 00:31:59,330
Fei…

721
00:32:06,030 --> 00:32:06,940
Why would I stay?

722
00:32:08,550 --> 00:32:09,660
This dock

723
00:32:10,790 --> 00:32:12,620
won't see another ship again.

724
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:25,860
You don't need to clean up.

725
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:27,940
Leave it till tomorrow.

726
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:25,420
Mentor…

727
00:33:28,920 --> 00:33:30,460
did I get it wrong again?

728
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:16,420
Let it go…

729
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:26,610
Let it be…

730
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,530
Those two characters
don't carry the same weight.

731
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:29,900
Cong,

732
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:32,210
Customs is not all-powerful.

733
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:34,260
We just do our best

734
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:35,490
within what's possible.

735
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:37,610
There will probably be regrets

736
00:36:37,630 --> 00:36:38,530
along the way,

737
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:40,570
but don't let those regrets

738
00:36:40,590 --> 00:36:41,490
make you doubt yourself.

739
00:36:41,630 --> 00:36:42,300
Okay?

740
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:16,940
Mentor.

741
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:19,860
Why are you here so early?

742
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:21,940
I was worried

743
00:38:22,070 --> 00:38:24,050
it'd be inconvenient to talk
once others showed up.

744
00:38:27,110 --> 00:38:28,170
You drank?

745
00:38:31,030 --> 00:38:31,650
A little.

746
00:38:35,110 --> 00:38:36,380
Help me turn that water off.

747
00:38:43,230 --> 00:38:44,130
How?

748
00:38:44,190 --> 00:38:45,130
The one on the left.

749
00:39:04,070 --> 00:39:04,780
Mentor,

750
00:39:06,590 --> 00:39:08,780
after I went home that day,

751
00:39:09,070 --> 00:39:10,900
I looked through Chen's notebook again.

752
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:15,570
I saw he wrote

753
00:39:15,710 --> 00:39:17,860
about you guys
picking up trash by the sea.

754
00:39:19,360 --> 00:39:20,380
Do you remember?

755
00:39:23,630 --> 00:39:24,420
I do.

756
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:27,090
Mr. Chen,

757
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:28,980
even when picking up trash,

758
00:39:29,030 --> 00:39:30,940
you still manage to connect it
to passenger inspection.

759
00:39:31,070 --> 00:39:32,050
Don't you have

760
00:39:32,150 --> 00:39:34,570
anything else in your head?

761
00:39:34,630 --> 00:39:35,980
Honestly? No.

762
00:39:37,630 --> 00:39:38,490
Why?

763
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:39,610
Because…

764
00:39:40,510 --> 00:39:41,170
my passion

765
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:43,420
for passenger inspection—

766
00:39:43,670 --> 00:39:45,530
if I have to put it dramatically—

767
00:39:46,070 --> 00:39:47,460
never fades!

768
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:05,690
I remember he was so happy that day.

769
00:40:05,710 --> 00:40:07,050
He kept laughing.

770
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:08,690
Those large trash bags.

771
00:40:08,710 --> 00:40:10,130
I filled ten of them.

772
00:40:10,230 --> 00:40:11,610
Just the bottles alone,

773
00:40:11,630 --> 00:40:12,900
I sold them for 50 yuan.

774
00:40:15,360 --> 00:40:16,170
Mentor,

775
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:18,380
when you talk about this,

776
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:19,860
there's light in your eyes.

777
00:40:20,630 --> 00:40:23,300
I feel like I went back to that time

778
00:40:23,360 --> 00:40:24,690
with you guys.

779
00:40:28,030 --> 00:40:28,650
Oh, right.

780
00:40:28,920 --> 00:40:30,130
A few months ago,

781
00:40:30,150 --> 00:40:32,170
at the nursing home,

782
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:34,260
Chen mentioned the same thing to me.

783
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:37,940
A few months ago?

784
00:40:39,710 --> 00:40:41,130
But his condition

785
00:40:41,710 --> 00:40:43,530
wasn't good by then.

786
00:40:44,320 --> 00:40:45,090
Yeah.

787
00:40:45,320 --> 00:40:47,690
But even like that,

788
00:40:47,920 --> 00:40:50,170
he still didn't forget
about trash and fish.

789
00:40:51,030 --> 00:40:52,860
So Chen would never give up.

790
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:55,050
Because fish need it.

791
00:40:56,920 --> 00:40:57,610
Mentor,

792
00:40:58,400 --> 00:41:00,210
Chen was never in a rush

793
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:02,940
because he believed

794
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:04,460
as long as we're still here,

795
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:05,980
no regret

796
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:07,300
is impossible to overcome.

797
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:21,130
And that day,

798
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:24,050
when I looked at the two characters
he left behind,

799
00:41:24,070 --> 00:41:25,050
I just kept feeling like…

800
00:41:27,630 --> 00:41:28,650
Those two words?

801
00:41:29,030 --> 00:41:29,900
What do you think?

802
00:41:31,230 --> 00:41:32,530
I think…

803
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:37,210
it might not have been
what he really meant.

804
00:41:39,230 --> 00:41:41,300
I flipped back and found

805
00:41:41,920 --> 00:41:42,380
that everything he wrote

806
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:44,690
was still about Customs.

807
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:46,980
If he had regrets
about the Group E case,

808
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:48,610
why didn't he write it down

809
00:41:48,630 --> 00:41:50,050
while he was still lucid?

810
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:51,900
Why wait until the very end

811
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:53,420
to suddenly write those two characters?

812
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:55,980
Was he confused again?

813
00:41:57,230 --> 00:41:58,210
Or…

814
00:42:00,070 --> 00:42:01,570
was something else influencing him?

815
00:42:08,190 --> 00:42:10,300
But Uncle Xiang told me

816
00:42:11,710 --> 00:42:13,380
my mentor said it to him directly.

817
00:42:14,510 --> 00:42:15,860
Mr. Xiang…

818
00:42:18,360 --> 00:42:20,460
Mr. Xiang…

819
00:42:22,070 --> 00:42:24,610
He isn't a doctor.

820
00:42:24,630 --> 00:42:27,610
How could he judge when Chen was lucid

821
00:42:27,630 --> 00:42:28,860
and when he wasn't?

822
00:42:30,960 --> 00:42:31,940
Besides,

823
00:42:32,070 --> 00:42:34,050
he was just retelling what he heard.

824
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:37,010
But you've got your own mind.

825
00:42:37,480 --> 00:42:39,340
Think about it yourself.

826
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:40,740
The same thing,

827
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:41,940
seen by different people,

828
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:43,380
can look completely different.

829
00:42:45,150 --> 00:42:46,530
I know what you're trying to say.

830
00:42:51,150 --> 00:42:52,050
Go home for now.

831
00:42:53,190 --> 00:42:53,860
I think…

832
00:42:54,960 --> 00:42:55,980
I need some time alone.

833
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:37,440
♪There's a place of simple,
everyday warmth♪

834
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:45,000
♪A door left open
for the wandering soul♪

835
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:52,440
♪A humble table still warm with love♪

836
00:43:52,640 --> 00:43:56,360
♪After you've tasted every high and low♪

837
00:43:56,560 --> 00:44:00,240
♪Come home, I'll keep you warm♪

838
00:44:00,960 --> 00:44:07,680
♪Where the days begin and end♪

839
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:15,320
♪A light still on for the ones
who've lost their way♪

840
00:44:16,120 --> 00:44:22,680
♪An embrace waiting just for you♪

841
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:26,680
♪Through every passing season♪

842
00:44:26,760 --> 00:44:30,640
♪Even if you return with nothing at all♪

843
00:44:31,080 --> 00:44:34,600
♪Turn around and look♪

844
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:38,600
♪That door's still open♪

845
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:42,440
♪A light still burning♪

846
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:46,240
♪Waiting there for you♪

847
00:44:46,440 --> 00:44:49,920
♪Turn around and look♪

848
00:44:50,160 --> 00:44:54,000
♪Someone's still waiting♪

849
00:44:54,120 --> 00:44:57,760
♪Watching the dusk settle in♪

850
00:44:57,840 --> 00:45:01,560
♪Waiting for the break of dawn♪

851
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:07,000
♪It's always there♪
